TEXT.0: This is the hourly-averaged data from the Apollo 15 Solar Wind Spectrometer

TEXT.1: instrument, reformatted by NSSDC for easier access and use.  During the lunar

TEXT.2: night there is no solar wind signal so there are data gaps of about 15 days

TEXT.5: Users should refer to the data set documentation paper entitled 'ALSEP solar wind spectrometer plasma data as observed at the Apollo 12 and 15 landing sites,' by Goldstein, Clay,Snyder, and Neugebauer, which is contained in the online Data Set Catalog at https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/nmc/publicationDisplay.do?id=B55381-000A

Logical_source_description.0: Apollo 15 Solar Wind measurements at the lunar surface

Acknowledgement.0: Please acknowledge Dr. Conway W. Snyder (JPL), and the NSSDC Lunar Data Project for providing these data.

LINK_TITLE.1: the Lunar Surface Origins Exploration service (LUNASOX)
